.TH "t3_sge_init_flcntxt" 9 "t3_sge_init_flcntxt" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
t3_sge_init_flcntxt \- initialize an SGE free-buffer list context
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" t3_sge_init_flcntxt
.BI "(struct adapter *adapter "  ","
.BI "unsigned int id "  ","
.BI "int gts_enable "  ","
.BI "u64 base_addr "  ","
.BI "unsigned int size "  ","
.BI "unsigned int bsize "  ","
.BI "unsigned int cong_thres "  ","
.BI "int gen "  ","
.BI "unsigned int cidx "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "adapter" 12
the adapter to configure
.IP "id" 12
the context id
.IP "gts_enable" 12
whether to enable GTS for the context
.IP "base_addr" 12
base address of queue
.IP "size" 12
number of queue entries
.IP "bsize" 12
size of each buffer for this queue
.IP "cong_thres" 12
threshold to signal congestion to upstream producers
.IP "gen" 12
initial generation value for the context
.IP "cidx" 12
consumer pointer

Initialize an SGE free list context and make it ready for use.  The
caller is responsible for ensuring only one context operation occurs
at a time.
